folder: Colonial Avenue & N. of 62nd Drive., Queens, NY
original_title: Queens: Colonial Avenue - N. of 62nd Drive.
text:
Colonial Ave., east side, north of 62nd Drive. In the foreground of view No. 1 is 62nd Drive at left where it makes a turn. It was then known (1922) as North Hempstead Plank Drive. The houses seen in the foreground belong to De La Corte who conducts an Inn here. In the background is the Flushing ash dump. The path at the right foreground became a part of 110th Street.

March 1925
View 2: Feb. 1925
View 3:4:1922
